# Variables & Constants in Go 🔥

(VERY IMPORTANT FOUNDATION)

---

# 1. Variables in Go 📦

Variable = data store karne ke liye memory container.

Example:

```go id="7b5i3q"
var name string = "Sourav"
```

---

# Syntax

```go id="gm2xvf"
var variableName dataType = value
```

---

# Example

```go id="ybgs8v"
var age int = 21
var city string = "Delhi"
```

---

# Short Declaration `:=` ⚡

Most used in Go.

```go id="z3t6zn"
name := "Sourav"
age := 21
```

Compiler automatically type detect karta hai.

---

# var vs := 🔥

| var                  | :=                |
| -------------------- | ----------------- |
| explicit declaration | short declaration |
| global + local       | only local        |
| type optional        | type auto infer   |
| longer               | shorter           |

---

# Example

## Using var

```go id="x1n38i"
var name string = "Go"
```

---

## Using :=

```go id="fg0wj7"
name := "Go"
```

---

# Important ⚠️

`:=` function ke bahar use nahi hota.

❌ Invalid:

```go id="r0cm0s"
name := "Sourav"
```

outside main/function.

---

# Correct

```go id="n7k3tw"
var name = "Sourav"
```

for global scope.

---

# Multiple Variables

```go id="7xq0bh"
var a, b, c int = 1, 2, 3
```

---

## Short Style

```go id="n90xqf"
x, y := 10, 20
```

---

# Zero Values 🔥

Agar value assign nahi ki:
Go default value deta hai.

| Type   | Zero Value |
| ------ | ---------- |
| int    | 0          |
| float  | 0.0        |
| string | ""         |
| bool   | false      |

---

# Example

```go id="zy3jvz"
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {

    var age int
    var name string
    var isLogin bool

    fmt.Println(age)
    fmt.Println(name)
    fmt.Println(isLogin)
}
```

---

# Output

```text id="8e9iwf"
0

false
```

(string empty print hoga)

